[Feature: Build the leave management module — Phase 10: Leave — service, controller, and routes]

Create src/modules/leave/leave.service.ts: implement ILeaveService as the orchestration hub. Constructor injects ILeaveRequestRepository (Phase 9), IEmployeeService (Phase 3), IPolicyService (Phase 4), IBalanceService (Phase 7), INotificationService (Phase 8), IAuditService (Phase 5). Implement submitLeaveRequest: validate employee is ACTIVE via IEmployeeService, validate entitlement via IPolicyService.validateEntitlement, create LeaveRequest via repository, record audit via IAuditService.recordAction, send notification via INotificationService.sendNotification. Implement approveLeaveRequest: transition status to APPROVED, deduct balance via IBalanceService.deductBalance, record audit, notify. Implement rejectLeaveRequest: transition to REJECTED, record audit, notify. Implement cancelLeaveRequest: transition to CANCELLED, restore balance via IBalanceService.restoreBalance if previously APPROVED, record audit, notify. All operations execute atomically within a single database transaction using the pg Pool from src/shared/db/connection.ts. Create src/modules/leave/leave.controller.ts: Fastify handlers with Zod validation (GP-003) and RBAC (GP-005). Create src/modules/leave/leave.routes.ts: register POST /leave/requests (submit), PATCH /leave/requests/:id/approve, PATCH /leave/requests/:id/reject, PATCH /leave/requests/:id/cancel, GET /leave/requests/:id, GET /leave/requests (list with LeaveRequestQueryParams). All async errors caught and mapped to HTTP responses (GP-006). Include Jest unit tests in tests/unit/modules/leave/.

This phase depends on: Phase 1, Phase 3, Phase 4, Phase 5, Phase 7, Phase 8, Phase 9.

Phase architecture notes:
The final phase. The leave service is the orchestration hub that wires together all other modules. Transactional integrity is critical — approve, reject, and cancel must atomically update the leave request status, mutate the balance, record audit, and send notification within a single database transaction.

